para_trans: The Maharashtra Employment Guarantee Act, 1977 regarding the reconstitution of the committee by partial changes in the committee at the panchayat level.
Government Decision No. SASUSU-2025 / No.87 / ROHIO-19
Madam Kama Marg, Martyr Rajguru Chowk,
Read: - 1) Government Decision No. Committee - 1001 / P.S. 360 / ROHYO-8, dated 09.04.2002.
2) Government Decision No.Magrarohayo-2010 / No.47 / Rohayo-10, dated 13.04.2023.

3) Revenue and Forest Department, Government Decision No. Work Plan 2025 / Q. 06 / M-8, dated 09.04.2025 Preamble: - As per Government Decision No. 1 of the aforesaid reference, a Panchayat Level Employment Guarantee Scheme Committee has been constituted under the Chairmanship of Member of Legislative Assembly. However, it was under the consideration of the Government to grant recognition to the Programme Officer declared under the Reference Government Decision No. 2 as a member for the overall and more effective functioning of the said Committee on the recommendation of the Study Group constituted under the Chairmanship of Divisional Commissioner, Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar as per the Reference Government Decision No. 3, accordingly, the Government is making the following orders. Similarly, the composition of the committee will be as follows.

Government Decision: - 1. Composition of Panchayat Level Employment Guarantee Scheme Committee As per Government Decision of Rohyo Ward, dated 09.04.2002, the composition of Panchayat Level Employment Guarantee Scheme Committees is as follows.

It now includes the above recommendations in the Committee constituted under the Chairmanship of the Member of Legislative Assembly vide Government Decision dated 09.04.2002 and includes the following members: -
table_trans: Member of Legislative Assembly elected from the constituency, Panchayat Member Committee elected by the Member of Legislative Assembly from the constituency if the Minister / Minister of State
Members of the Legislative Council residing in the Panchayat Samiti area
Two representatives of the workers working in the scheme work or the agricultural labor union

para_trans: 3. The meeting of the aforesaid Committee shall be held after the meetings of the Taluka Coordination Committee so as to avoid wastage of time and to carry out the affairs of the Committee more effectively.
4. After the reconstitution of the Committee as aforesaid, Reference No. All inquiries into the Government Decision dated 09.04.2002, dated 1st April, shall stand.
The decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website at www.maharashtra.gov.in.
